summary:
In quantum mechanics, bra–ket notation, or Dirac notation, is used ubiquitously to denote quantum states. The notation uses angle brackets, 



        ⟨


    {\displaystyle \langle }

 and 



        ⟩


    {\displaystyle \rangle }

, and a vertical bar 




          |



    {\displaystyle |}

, to construct "bras" and "kets".
